      • getHeaderType

        public de.esoco.lib.property.ListLayoutStyle getHeaderType()
        Returns the expand style of this header. The default implementation returns ListLayoutStyle.SIMPLE which will display a non-expandable header and the method initDataPanel(InteractionFragment) will not be invoked. Subclasses that want to use an expandable header panel must override this method and return a different style.
        Returns:
        The header layout style

      • addExpandableHeaderIndicator

        protected Parameter<java.lang.String> addExpandableHeaderIndicator(InteractionFragment rHeaderPanel)

        Parameters:
        rHeaderPanel - The header panel
        Returns:
        The parameter representing the indicator

      • toggleSorting

        protected de.esoco.lib.property.SortDirection toggleSorting(org.obrel.core.RelationType<?> rSortColumn,
                                                            de.esoco.lib.property.SortDirection eDirection)
        Toggles the sorting of a certain column attribute by switching through the states ascending, descending, and no sorting. This will change the style of the sort column header accordingly.
        Parameters:
        rSortColumn - The new sort column or NULL for no sorting
        eDirection - The sort direction to set or NULL to switch an existing direction
        Returns:
        The current style of the sorted column (NULL for not sorted)
